      "comment": "BASEMENT (5) is a talented type and proved too strong last time to win by a neck at Bendigo in a handy 24.33 beating Sandy Cheek. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in his latest win. Can measure up again. NORBIT (8) was beaten for speed from wide out but attacked the line strongly to place, 3 lengths from the winner (25.93) at this track in Grade 5. Expecting another good run. PAW HARRY (2) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing seventh (29.10) last time in a Grade 5 at Bendigo. Has a good record at this journey. Goes well out of this box with a win and seven minor placings. One of the main contenders. LILLY LOUD MOUTH (1) can sneak into the finish.",
